xboing (1.0.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix the between-level bonus interstitial reporting the wrong high-score
    rank (e.g. "1st" when the player finished 2nd). It now predicts
    placement against the board the player competes on (personal when no
    global board exists) using the same slot logic as the actual insert.
    Also stop prompting for boing-master "words of wisdom" on installs with
    no global board, where the text was silently discarded. (ADR-050.)

 -- J Freeman <jmf@pobox.com>  Tue, 30 Jun 2026 11:35:15 -0700

xboing (1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * First stable release of the SDL2 modernization (1.0). Includes the
    SDL2-accurate man page, the -scores fix for non-Debian platforms, and
    the README/install rework. Version is single-sourced from
    project(VERSION) and matches the v1.0 git tag and the Homebrew formula.

 -- J Freeman <jmf@pobox.com>  Mon, 29 Jun 2026 17:41:01 -0700

xboing (0.9-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Re-version the SDL2 modernization to 0.9 (pre-1.0). The "2.4" of the
    entries below is the original 1993-1996 Xlib game's version, kept as
    heritage; this is the first numbered release of the modern port and
    matches the v0.9 git tag and the Homebrew formula.

 -- Justin Freeman <jmf@pobox.com>  Sun, 28 Jun 2026 21:00:00 +0000

xboing (2.4-2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Rename the installed binary to /usr/games/xboing (was xboing_sdl2
    with a symlink workaround in /usr/bin); CMake now installs the target
    directly, with debian/rules overriding bindir to games per Debian
    Policy 11.5.
  * Remove debian/compat — duplicated debhelper-compat (= 13) from
    debian/control's Build-Depends and prevented dpkg-buildpackage from
    running.  The .deb is now actually buildable.
  * Add explicit pkg-config Build-Depends (was relied on transitively
    via libsdl2-dev).
  * Update debian/copyright: original/ stays under the 1993-1996 X
    Consortium-style license (Justin C. Kibell); the SDL2 modernization
    is MIT (J Freeman, 2025-2026).
  * Implement -help / -version / -setup / -scores in the SDL2 binary
    (previously they parsed but exited silently with no output).
  * Add a top-level convenience Makefile wrapping cmake / ctest /
    dpkg-buildpackage.

 -- J Freeman <jmf@pobox.com>  Sun, 26 Apr 2026 17:00:00 -0700

